# Figma CLI - Cursor Integration

You have access to a CLI that controls Figma Desktop directly via Chrome DevTools Protocol. No API key needed. Use the Shell tool to run commands.

## Base Command

All commands start with: `node src/index.js` (run from the figma-cli project root at /Users/sajal.k/Documents/FigmaClaudeCode/figma-cli)

## Quick Reference

| User says | Command |
|-----------|---------|
| "connect to figma" | `node src/index.js connect` |
| "connect safe mode" | `node src/index.js connect --safe` |
| "add shadcn colors" | `node src/index.js tokens preset shadcn` |
| "add tailwind colors" | `node src/index.js tokens tailwind` |
| "show colors on canvas" | `node src/index.js var visualize` |
| "create dashboard" | `node src/index.js blocks create dashboard-01` |
| "list variables" | `node src/index.js var list` |
| "find nodes named X" | `node src/index.js find "X"` |
| "what's on canvas" | `node src/index.js canvas info` |
| "export as PNG/SVG" | `node src/index.js export png` |
| "check accessibility" | `node src/index.js lint` |
| "verify creation" | `node src/index.js verify` |

## Connection

```bash
node src/index.js connect          # Yolo Mode (patches Figma, direct CDP)
node src/index.js connect --safe   # Safe Mode (plugin bridge, no patching)
node src/index.js status           # Check connection
node src/index.js mahoraga status   # Check mahoraga
```

## Dropping Components

```bash
node src/index.js drop list                    # List all drops
node src/index.js drop list -c android         # Filter by category
node src/index.js drop in android bottom-sheet # Drop onto canvas
node src/index.js drop in fab                  # Aliases work
```

When user says "drop in a ..." or "add a ...", use `drop in <name>`.

### Save & Reuse

When user creates something and says "save this as a drop":
```bash
node src/index.js drop save "My Card"                  # Save selection
node src/index.js drop save "Header" -c layout -a hero # With category + alias
node src/index.js drop remove my-card                  # Remove saved drop
```

## Creating Elements

```bash
node src/index.js create rect "Card" -w 320 -h 200 --fill "#fff" --radius 12
node src/index.js create circle "Avatar" -w 48 --fill "#3b82f6"
node src/index.js create text "Hello" -s 24 -c "#000" -w bold
node src/index.js create line -l 200 -c "#e4e4e7"
node src/index.js create autolayout "Card" -d col -g 16 -p 24 --fill "#fff"
node src/index.js create icon lucide:star -s 24 -c "#f59e0b"
node src/index.js create frame "Section" --fill "var:background"
```

## JSX Rendering (Complex Layouts)

Use `render` for complex multi-element layouts:

```bash
node src/index.js render '<Frame name="Card" w={320} h={200} bg="#18181b" rounded={12} flex="col" p={24} gap={12}>
  <Text size={18} weight="bold" color="#fff">Title</Text>
  <Text size={14} color="#a1a1aa" w="fill">Description text</Text>
  <Frame bg="#3b82f6" px={16} py={8} rounded={6} flex="row" justify="center" items="center">
    <Text size={14} weight="medium" color="#fff">Button</Text>
  </Frame>
</Frame>'
```

### JSX Props

- **Layout**: `flex="row"|"col"`, `gap={16}`, `p={24}`, `px={16}`, `py={8}`
- **Alignment**: `justify="center"|"start"|"end"|"between"`, `items="center"|"start"|"end"`
- **Size**: `w={320}`, `h={200}`, `w="fill"`, `h="fill"`, `grow={1}`
- **Appearance**: `bg="#fff"`, `bg="var:card"`, `stroke="#000"`, `rounded={12}`, `opacity={0.8}`
- **Text**: `<Text size={18} weight="bold" color="#fff" w="fill">Content</Text>`
- **Icons**: `<Icon name="lucide:home" size={20} color="#fff" />`
- **Slots**: `<Slot name="Content" flex="col" gap={8} />`

### Variable Binding (var: syntax)

Bind to design tokens inline: `bg="var:card"`, `color="var:foreground"`, `stroke="var:border"`

Available shadcn variables: `background`, `foreground`, `card`, `card-foreground`, `primary`, `primary-foreground`, `secondary`, `secondary-foreground`, `muted`, `muted-foreground`, `accent`, `accent-foreground`, `border`, `input`, `ring`

## Design Tokens

```bash
node src/index.js tokens preset shadcn    # 276 vars with Light/Dark mode
node src/index.js tokens tailwind         # Tailwind color palette
node src/index.js tokens ds               # IDS Base colors
node src/index.js var list                # List all variables
node src/index.js var delete-all          # Delete all variables
```

## shadcn Components

```bash
node src/index.js shadcn list             # List available components
node src/index.js shadcn add --all        # Generate all 30 components
node src/index.js shadcn add button card input tabs  # Specific ones
```

## Modify Elements

```bash
node src/index.js set fill "#3b82f6"       # Set fill color
node src/index.js set fill "var:primary"   # Bind to variable
node src/index.js set stroke "var:border"
node src/index.js set radius 12
node src/index.js select "1:234"           # Select by ID
node src/index.js delete "1:234"           # Delete node
node src/index.js duplicate "1:234"        # Duplicate
```

## Find & Query

```bash
node src/index.js find "Button"            # Find by name
node src/index.js find --type COMPONENT    # Find by type
node src/index.js get "1:234"              # Get node properties
node src/index.js canvas info              # Canvas overview
```

## Export

```bash
node src/index.js export png               # Export as PNG
node src/index.js export svg               # Export as SVG
node src/index.js verify                   # Screenshot for verification
```

## Eval (Run Raw Figma Plugin API)

```bash
node src/index.js eval "figma.currentPage.children.map(n => n.name)"
```

## Critical Rules

1. **Always use `render` for complex layouts** - has smart positioning
2. **Never use `eval` to create elements** - no positioning, overlaps at (0,0)
3. **Text wrapping**: ALL Text elements need `w="fill"` to wrap properly
4. **Use real Lucide icons**: `<Icon name="lucide:home" />` not emojis
5. **After creation**: Run `node src/index.js verify` to validate visually
6. **Never delete existing nodes** without user permission
